ReadMe
======

This portion of the monorepo is the backend for `ReadMe`, a student productivity tool for balancing the texts you want to read versus the ones you need to.

The backend is a minimal Python + FastAPI API using SQLModel for database access.

Setup
=====

The API expects a Postgres database. By default, it connects to Postgres on `127.0.0.1:5432`, which is the same mapping as in the `docker-compose.yml` file in the root of the monorepo.

Run locally
-----------

1) Start Postgres

+----
|    docker compose up -d db
+----

2) Install backend dependencies and start the API:

+----
|    cd backend
|    python -m venv .venv
|    source .venv/bin/activate
|    pip install -r requirements.txt
|    uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8000
+----

Run with Docker Compose
-----------------------

+----
|    docker compose up -d
+----

Usage
=====

When the app is running, navigate to `http://localhost:8000/docs` for API documentation.

Links
=====

* GitHub Repository: https://github.com/lachlanharrisdev/readme
